body.input: national_number:4, gen:I, name:Charmander, primary_type:fire, classification:Lizard Pokémon, height_m:0.6, weight_kg:8.5, abilities:Blaze, description:It has a preference for hot things. When it rains, steam is said to spout from the tip of its tail.

national_number:5, gen:I, name:Charmeleon, primary_type:fire, classification:Flame Pokémon, height_m:1.1, weight_kg:19, abilities:Blaze, description:It has a barbaric nature. In battle, it whips its fiery tail around and slashes away with sharp claws.

national_number:6, gen:I, name:Charizard, primary_type:fire, secondary_type:flying, classification:Flame Pokémon, height_m:1.7, weight_kg:90.5, abilities:Blaze, description:It spits fire that is hot enough to melt boulders. It may cause forest fires by blowing flames.

national_number:7, gen:I, name:Squirtle, primary_type:water, classification:Tiny Turtle Pokémon, height_m:0.5, weight_kg:9, abilities:Torrent, description:When it retracts its long neck into its shell, it squirts out water with vigorous force.

national_number:8, gen:I, name:Wartortle, primary_type:water, classification:Turtle Pokémon, height_m:1, weight_kg:22.5, abilities:Torrent, description:It is recognized as a symbol of longevity. If its shell has algae on it, that Wartortle is very old.

national_number:9, gen:I, name:Blastoise, primary_type:water, classification:Shellfish Pokémon, height_m:1.6, weight_kg:85.5, abilities:Torrent, description:It crushes its foe under its heavy body to cause fainting. In a pinch, it will withdraw inside its shell.

national_number:10, gen:I, name:Caterpie, primary_type:bug, classification:Worm Pokémon, height_m:0.3, weight_kg:2.9, abilities:Shield Dust, description:For protection, it releases a horrible stench from the antenna on its head to drive away enemies.

national_number:11, gen:I, name:Metapod, primary_type:bug, classification:Cocoon Pokémon, height_m:0.7, weight_kg:9.9, abilities:Shed Skin, description:It is waiting for the moment to evolve. At this stage, it can only harden, so it remains motionless to avoid attack.

national_number:12, gen:I, name:Butterfree, primary_type:bug, secondary_type:flying, classification:Butterfly Pokémon, height_m:1.1, weight_kg:32, abilities:Compoundeyes, description:In battle, it flaps its wings at great speed to release highly toxic dust into the air.

national_number:13, gen:I, name:Weedle, primary_type:bug, secondary_type:poison, classification:Hairy Pokémon, height_m:0.3, weight_kg:3.2, abilities:Shield Dust, description:Beware of the sharp stinger on its head. It hides in grass and bushes where it eats leaves.

national_number:14, gen:I, name:Kakuna, primary_type:bug, secondary_type:poison, classification:Cocoon Pokémon, height_m:0.6, weight_kg:10, abilities:Shed Skin, description:Able to move only slightly. When endangered, it may stick out its stinger and poison its enemy.

national_number:15, gen:I, name:Beedrill, primary_type:bug, secondary_type:poison, classification:Poison Bee Pokémon, height_m:1, weight_kg:29.5, abilities:Swarm, description:It has three poisonous stingers on its forelegs and its tail. They are used to jab its enemy repeatedly.

national_number:16, gen:I, name:Pidgey, primary_type:normal, secondary_type:flying, classification:Tiny Bird Pokémon, height_m:0.3, weight_kg:1.8, abilities:Keen Eye, description:Very docile. If attacked, it will often kick up sand to protect itself rather than fight back.

national_number:17, gen:I, name:Pidgeotto, primary_type:normal, secondary_type:flying, classification:Bird Pokémon, height_m:1.1, weight_kg:30, abilities:Keen Eye, description:This Pokémon is full of vitality. It constantly flies around its large territory in search of prey.

national_number:18, gen:I, name:Pidgeot, primary_type:normal, secondary_type:flying, classification:Bird Pokémon, height_m:1.5, weight_kg:39.5, abilities:Keen Eye, description:This Pokémon flies at Mach 2 speed, seeking prey. Its large talons are feared as wicked weapons.

national_number:19, gen:I, name:Rattata, primary_type:normal, secondary_type:dark, classification:Mouse Pokémon, height_m:0.3, weight_kg:3.5, abilities:Run Away, description:Will chew on anything with its fangs. If you see one, you can be certain that 40 more live in the area.

national_number:20, gen:I, name:Raticate, primary_type:normal, secondary_type:dark, classification:Mouse Pokémon, height_m:0.7, weight_kg:18.5, abilities:Run Away, description:Its hind feet are webbed. They act as flippers, so it can swim in rivers and hunt for prey.

national_number:21, gen:I, name:Spearow, primary_type:normal, secondary_type:flying, classification:Tiny Bird Pokémon, height_m:0.3, weight_kg:2, abilities:Keen Eye, description:Inept at flying high. However, it can fly around very fast to protect its territory.

national_number:22, gen:I, name:Fearow, primary_type:normal, secondary_type:flying, classification:Beak Pokémon, height_m:1.2, weight_kg:38, abilities:Keen Eye, description:A Pokémon that dates back many years. If it senses danger, it flies high and away, instantly.

national_number:23, gen:I, name:Ekans, primary_type:poison, classification:Snake Pokémon, height_m:2, weight_kg:6.9, abilities:Intimidate, description:The older it gets, the longer it grows. At night, it wraps its long body around tree branches to rest.

national_number:24, gen:I, name:Arbok, primary_type:poison, classification:Cobra Pokémon, height_m:3.5, weight_kg:65, abilities:Intimidate, description:The frightening patterns on its belly have been studied. Six variations have been confirmed.

national_number:25, gen:I, name:Pikachu, primary_type:electric, classification:Mouse Pokémon, height_m:0.4, weight_kg:6, abilities:Static, description:Pikachu that can generate powerful electricity have cheek sacs that are extra soft and super stretchy.

national_number:26, gen:I, name:Raichu, primary_type:electric, secondary_type:electric, classification:Mouse Pokémon, height_m:0.8, weight_kg:30, abilities:Static, description:Its long tail serves as a ground to protect itself from its own high-voltage power.

national_number:27, gen:I, name:Sandshrew, primary_type:ground, secondary_type:ice, classification:Mouse Pokémon, height_m:0.6, weight_kg:12, abilities:Sand Veil, description:It loves to bathe in the grit of dry, sandy areas. By sand bathing, the Pokémon rids itself of dirt and moisture clinging to its body.

national_number:28, gen:I, name:Sandslash, primary_type:ground, secondary_type:ice, classification:Mouse Pokémon, height_m:1, weight_kg:29.5, abilities:Sand Veil, description:The drier the area Sandslash lives in, the harder and smoother the Pokémon's spikes will feel when touched.

national_number:29, gen:I, name:Nidoran♀, primary_type:poison, classification:Poison Pin Pokémon, height_m:0.4, weight_kg:7, abilities:Poison Point, description:Females are more sensitive to smells than males. While foraging, they'll use their whiskers to check wind direction and stay downwind of predators.

national_number:30, gen:I, name:Nidorina, primary_type:poison, classification:Poison Pin Pokémon, height_m:0.8, weight_kg:20, abilities:Poison Point, description:The horn on its head has atrophied. L thought that this happens so Nidorina's children won't get poked while their mother is feeding them.

national_number:31, gen:I, name:Nidoqueen, primary_type:poison, secondary_type:ground, classification:Drill Pokémon, height_m:1.3, weight_kg:60, abilities:Poison Point, description:Nidoqueen is better at defense than offense. With scales like armor, this Pokémon will shield its children from any kind of attack.

national_number:32, gen:I, name:Nidoran♂, primary_type:poison, classification:Poison Pin Pokémon, height_m:0.5, weight_kg:9, abilities:Poison Point, description:The horn on a male Nidoran's forehead contains a powerful poison. This is a very cautious Pokémon, always straining its large ears.

national_number:33, gen:I, name:Nidorino, primary_type:poison, classification:Poison Pin Pokémon, height_m:0.9, weight_kg:19.5, abilities:Poison Point, description:With a horn that's harder than diamond, this Pokémon goes around shattering boulders as it searches for a moon stone.

national_number:34, gen:I, name:Nidoking, primary_type:poison, secondary_type:ground, classification:Drill Pokémon, height_m:1.4, weight_kg:62, abilities:Poison Point, description:When it goes on a rampage, L impossible to control. But in the presence of a Nidoqueen L lived with for a long time, Nidoking calms down.

national_number:35, gen:I, name:Clefairy, primary_type:fairy, classification:Fairy Pokémon, height_m:0.6, weight_kg:7.5, abilities:Cute Charm, description:It is said that happiness will come to those who see a gathering of Clefairy dancing under a full moon.

national_number:36, gen:I, name:Clefable, primary_type:fairy, classification:Fairy Pokémon, height_m:1.3, weight_kg:40, abilities:Cute Charm, description:A timid fairy Pokémon that is rarely seen, it will run and hide the moment it senses people.

national_number:37, gen:I, name:Vulpix, primary_type:fire, secondary_type:ice, classification:Fox Pokémon, height_m:0.6, weight_kg:9.9, abilities:Flash Fire, description:While young, it has six gorgeous tails. When it grows, several new tails are sprouted.

national_number:38, gen:I, name:Ninetales, primary_type:fire, secondary_type:ice, classification:Fox Pokémon, height_m:1.1, weight_kg:19.9, abilities:Flash Fire, description:It is said to live 1,000 years, and each of its tails is loaded with supernatural powers.

national_number:39, gen:I, name:Jigglypuff, primary_type:normal, secondary_type:fairy, classification:Balloon Pokémon, height_m:0.5, weight_kg:5.5, abilities:Cute Charm, description:Jigglypuff has top-notch lung capacity, even by comparison to other Pokémon. It won't stop singing its lullabies until its foes fall asleep.

national_number:40, gen:I, name:Wigglytuff, primary_type:normal, secondary_type:fairy, classification:Balloon Pokémon, height_m:1, weight_kg:12, abilities:Cute Charm, description:The more air it takes in, the more it inflates. If opponents catch it in a bad mood, it will inflate itself to an enormous size to intimidate them.

national_number:41, gen:I, name:Zubat, primary_type:poison, secondary_type:flying, classification:Bat Pokémon, height_m:0.8, weight_kg:7.5, abilities:Inner Focus, description:It emits ultrasonic waves from its mouth to check its surroundings. Even in tight caves, Zubat flies around with skill.

national_number:42, gen:I, name:Golbat, primary_type:poison, secondary_type:flying, classification:Bat Pokémon, height_m:1.6, weight_kg:55, abilities:Inner Focus, description:It loves to drink other creatures' blood. L said that if it finds others of its kind going hungry, it sometimes shares the blood L gathered.

national_number:43, gen:I, name:Oddish, primary_type:grass, secondary_type:poison, classification:Weed Pokémon, height_m:0.5, weight_kg:5.4, abilities:Chlorophyll, description:If exposed to moonlight, it starts to move. It roams far and wide at night to scatter its seeds.

national_number:44, gen:I, name:Gloom, primary_type:grass, secondary_type:poison, classification:Weed Pokémon, height_m:0.8, weight_kg:8.6, abilities:Chlorophyll, description:Its pistils exude an incredibly foul odor. The horrid stench can cause fainting at a distance of 1.25 miles.

national_number:45, gen:I, name:Vileplume, primary_type:grass, secondary_type:poison, classification:Flower Pokémon, height_m:1.2, weight_kg:18.6, abilities:Chlorophyll, description:It has the world's largest petals. With every step, the petals shake out heavy clouds of toxic pollen.

national_number:46, gen:I, name:Paras, primary_type:bug, secondary_type:grass, classification:Mushroom Pokémon, height_m:0.3, weight_kg:5.4, abilities:Effect Spore, description:Burrows under the ground to gnaw on tree roots. The mushrooms on its back absorb most of the nutrition.

national_number:47, gen:I, name:Parasect, primary_type:bug, secondary_type:grass, classification:Mushroom Pokémon, height_m:1, weight_kg:29.5, abilities:Effect Spore, description:The bug host is drained of energy by the mushroom on its back. The mushroom appears to do all the thinking.

national_number:48, gen:I, name:Venonat, primary_type:bug, secondary_type:poison, classification:Insect Pokémon, height_m:1, weight_kg:30, abilities:Compound Eyes, description:Its large eyes act as radar. In a bright place, you can see that they are clusters of many tiny eyes.

national_number:49, gen:I, name:Venomoth, primary_type:bug, secondary_type:poison, classification:Poison Moth Pokémon, height_m:1.5, weight_kg:12.5, abilities:Shield Dust, description:The powdery scales on its wings are hard to remove from skin. They also contain poison that leaks out on contact.

national_number:50, gen:I, name:Diglett, primary_type:ground, secondary_type:ground, classification:Mole Pokémon, height_m:0.2, weight_kg:0.8, abilities:Sand Veil, description:If a Diglett digs through a field, it leaves the soil perfectly tilled and ideal for planting crops.

national_number:51, gen:I, name:Dugtrio, primary_type:ground, secondary_type:ground, classification:Mole Pokémon, height_m:0.7, weight_kg:33.3, abilities:Sand Veil, description:A team of Diglett triplets. It triggers huge earthquakes by burrowing 60 miles underground.

national_number:52, gen:I, name:Meowth, primary_type:normal, secondary_type:dark, classification:Scratch Cat Pokémon, height_m:0.4, weight_kg:4.2, abilities:Pickup, description:It loves to collect shiny things. If L in a good mood, it might even let its Trainer have a look at its hoard of treasures.

national_number:53, gen:I, name:Persian, primary_type:normal, secondary_type:dark, classification:Classy Cat Pokémon, height_m:1, weight_kg:32, abilities:Limber, description:Getting this prideful Pokémon to warm up to you takes a lot of effort, and it will claw at you the moment it gets annoyed.

national_number:54, gen:I, name:Psyduck, primary_type:water, classification:Duck Pokémon, height_m:0.8, weight_kg:19.6, abilities:Damp, description:Psyduck is constantly beset by headaches. If the Pokémon lets its strange power erupt, apparently the pain subsides for a while.

national_number:55, gen:I, name:Golduck, primary_type:water, classification:Duck Pokémon, height_m:1.7, weight_kg:76.6, abilities:Damp, description:This Pokémon lives in gently flowing rivers. It paddles through the water with its long limbs, putting its graceful swimming skills on display.

national_number:56, gen:I, name:Mankey, primary_type:fighting, classification:Pig Monkey Pokémon, height_m:0.5, weight_kg:28, abilities:Vital Spirit, description:An agile Pokémon that lives in trees. It angers easily and will not hesitate to attack anything.

national_number:57, gen:I, name:Primeape, primary_type:fighting, classification:Pig Monkey Pokémon, height_m:1, weight_kg:32, abilities:Vital Spirit, description:It stops being angry only when nobody else is around. To view this moment is very difficult.

national_number:58, gen:I, name:Growlithe, primary_type:fire, classification:Puppy Pokémon, height_m:0.7, weight_kg:19, abilities:Intimidate, description:It has a brave and trustworthy nature. It fearlessly stands up to bigger and stronger foes.

national_number:59, gen:I, name:Arcanine, primary_type:fire, classification:Legendary Pokémon, height_m:1.9, weight_kg:155, abilities:Intimidate, description:The sight of it running over 6,200 miles in a single day and night has captivated many people.

national_number:60, gen:I, name:Poliwag, primary_type:water, classification:Tadpole Pokémon, height_m:0.6, weight_kg:12.4, abilities:Water Absorb, description:For Poliwag, swimming is easier than walking. The swirl pattern on its belly is actually part of the Pokémon's innards showing through the skin.

national_number:61, gen:I, name:Poliwhirl, primary_type:water, classification:Tadpole Pokémon, height_m:1, weight_kg:20, abilities:Water Absorb, description:Staring at the swirl on its belly causes drowsiness. This trait of Poliwhirl's has been used in place of lullabies to get children to go to sleep.

national_number:62, gen:I, name:Poliwrath, primary_type:water, secondary_type:fighting, classification:Tadpole Pokémon, height_m:1.3, weight_kg:54, abilities:Water Absorb, description:Its body is solid muscle. When swimming through cold seas, Poliwrath uses its impressive arms to smash through drift ice and plow forward.

national_number:63, gen:I, name:Abra, primary_type:psychic, classification:Psi Pokémon, height_m:0.9, weight_kg:19.5, abilities:Synchronize, description:This Pokémon uses its psychic powers while it sleeps. The contents of Abra's dreams affect the powers that the Pokémon wields.

national_number:64, gen:I, name:Kadabra, primary_type:psychic, classification:Psi Pokémon, height_m:1.3, weight_kg:56.5, abilities:Synchronize, description:Using its psychic power, Kadabra levitates as it sleeps. It uses its springy tail as a pillow.

national_number:65, gen:I, name:Alakazam, primary_type:psychic, classification:Psi Pokémon, height_m:1.5, weight_kg:48, abilities:Synchronize, description:It has an incredibly high level of intelligence. Some say that Alakazam remembers everything that ever happens to it, from birth till death.

national_number:66, gen:I, name:Machop, primary_type:fighting, classification:Superpower Pokémon, height_m:0.8, weight_kg:19.5, abilities:Guts, description:Its whole body is composed of muscles. Even though L the size of a human child, it can hurl 100 grown-ups.

national_number:67, gen:I, name:Machoke, primary_type:fighting, classification:Superpower Pokémon, height_m:1.5, weight_kg:70.5, abilities:Guts, description:Its muscular body is so powerful, it must wear a power-save belt to be able to regulate its motions.

national_number:68, gen:I, name:Machamp, primary_type:fighting, classification:Superpower Pokémon, height_m:1.6, weight_kg:130, abilities:Guts, description:It quickly swings its four arms to rock its opponents with ceaseless punches and chops from all angles.

national_number:69, gen:I, name:Bellsprout, primary_type:grass, secondary_type:poison, classification:Flower Pokémon, height_m:0.7, weight_kg:4, abilities:Chlorophyll, description:Prefers hot and humid places. It ensnares tiny bugs with its vines and devours them.

national_number:70, gen:I, name:Weepinbell, primary_type:grass, secondary_type:poison, classification:Flycatcher Pokémon, height_m:1, weight_kg:6.4, abilities:Chlorophyll, description:When hungry, it swallows anything that moves. Its hapless prey is dissolved by strong acids.

national_number:71, gen:I, name:Victreebel, primary_type:grass, secondary_type:poison, classification:Flycatcher Pokémon, height_m:1.7, weight_kg:15.5, abilities:Chlorophyll, description:Lures prey with the sweet aroma of honey. Swallowed whole, the prey is dissolved in a day, bones and all.

national_number:72, gen:I, name:Tentacool, primary_type:water, secondary_type:poison, classification:Jellyfish Pokémon, height_m:0.9, weight_kg:45.5, abilities:Clear Body, description:Tentacool is not a particularly strong swimmer. It drifts across the surface of shallow seas as it searches for prey.

national_number:73, gen:I, name:Tentacruel, primary_type:water, secondary_type:poison, classification:Jellyfish Pokémon, height_m:1.6, weight_kg:55, abilities:Clear Body, description:When the red orbs on Tentacruel's head glow brightly, watch out. The Pokémon is about to fire off a burst of ultrasonic waves.

national_number:74, gen:I, name:Geodude, primary_type:rock, secondary_type:ground, classification:Rock Pokémon, height_m:0.4, weight_kg:20, abilities:Rock Head, description:Commonly found near mountain trails and the like. If you step on one by accident, it gets angry.

national_number:75, gen:I, name:Graveler, primary_type:rock, secondary_type:ground, classification:Rock Pokémon, height_m:1, weight_kg:105, abilities:Rock Head, description:Often seen rolling down mountain trails. Obstacles are just things to roll straight over, not avoid.

national_number:76, gen:I, name:Golem, primary_type:rock, secondary_type:ground, classification:Megaton Pokémon, height_m:1.4, weight_kg:300, abilities:Rock Head, description:Once it sheds its skin, its body turns tender and whitish. Its hide hardens when L exposed to air.

national_number:77, gen:I, name:Ponyta, primary_type:fire, secondary_type:psychic, classification:Fire Horse Pokémon, height_m:1, weight_kg:30, abilities:Run Away, description:It can't run properly when L newly born. As it races around with others of its kind, its legs grow stronger.

national_number:78, gen:I, name:Rapidash, primary_type:fire, secondary_type:psychic, classification:Fire Horse Pokémon, height_m:1.7, weight_kg:95, abilities:Run Away, description:This Pokémon can be seen galloping through fields at speeds of up to 150 mph, its fiery mane fluttering in the wind.

national_number:79, gen:I, name:Slowpoke, primary_type:water, secondary_type:psychic, classification:Dopey Pokémon, height_m:1.2, weight_kg:36, abilities:Oblivious, description:Slow-witted and oblivious, this Pokémon won't feel any pain if its tail gets eaten. It won't notice when its tail grows back, either.

national_number:80, gen:I, name:Slowbro, primary_type:water, secondary_type:psychic, classification:Hermit Crab Pokémon, height_m:1.6, weight_kg:78.5, abilities:Oblivious, description:Slowpoke became Slowbro when a Shellder bit on to its tail. Sweet flavors seeping from the tail make the Shellder feel as if its life is a dream.

national_number:81, gen:I, name:Magnemite, primary_type:electric, secondary_type:steel, classification:Magnet Pokémon, height_m:0.3, weight_kg:6, abilities:Magnet Pull, description:At times, Magnemite runs out of electricity and ends up on the ground. If you give batteries to a grounded Magnemite, it'll start moving again.

national_number:82, gen:I, name:Magneton, primary_type:electric, secondary_type:steel, classification:Magnet Pokémon, height_m:1, weight_kg:60, abilities:Magnet Pull, description:This Pokémon is three Magnemite that have linked together. Magneton sends out powerful radio waves to study its surroundings.

national_number:83, gen:I, name:Farfetch'd, primary_type:normal, secondary_type:flying, classification:Wild Duck Pokémon, height_m:0.8, weight_kg:15, abilities:Keen Eye, description:The stalk this Pokémon carries in its wings serves as a sword to cut down opponents. In a dire situation, the stalk can also serve as food.

national_number:84, gen:I, name:Doduo, primary_type:normal, secondary_type:flying, classification:Twin Bird Pokémon, height_m:1.4, weight_kg:39.2, abilities:Run Away, description:Its short wings make flying difficult. Instead, this Pokémon runs at high speed on developed legs.

national_number:85, gen:I, name:Dodrio, primary_type:normal, secondary_type:flying, classification:Triple Bird Pokémon, height_m:1.8, weight_kg:85.2, abilities:Run Away, description:One of Doduo's two heads splits to form a unique species. It runs close to 40 mph in prairies.

national_number:86, gen:I, name:Seel, primary_type:water, classification:Sea Lion Pokémon, height_m:1.1, weight_kg:90, abilities:Thick Fat, description:Loves freezing-cold conditions. Relishes swimming in a frigid climate of around 14 degrees Fahrenheit.

national_number:87, gen:I, name:Dewgong, primary_type:water, secondary_type:ice, classification:Sea Lion Pokémon, height_m:1.7, weight_kg:120, abilities:Thick Fat, description:Its entire body is a snowy white. Unharmed by even intense cold, it swims powerfully in icy waters.

national_number:88, gen:I, name:Grimer, primary_type:poison, secondary_type:poison, classification:Sludge Pokémon, height_m:0.9, weight_kg:30, abilities:Stench, description:Made of congealed sludge. It smells too putrid to touch. Even weeds won't grow in its path.

national_number:89, gen:I, name:Muk, primary_type:poison, secondary_type:poison, classification:Sludge Pokémon, height_m:1.2, weight_kg:30, abilities:Stench, description:Smells so awful, it can cause fainting. Through degeneration of its nose, it lost its sense of smell.

national_number:90, gen:I, name:Shellder, primary_type:water, classification:Bivalve Pokémon, height_m:0.3, weight_kg:4, abilities:Shell Armor, description:It swims facing backward by opening and closing its two-piece shell. It is surprisingly fast.

national_number:91, gen:I, name:Cloyster, primary_type:water, secondary_type:ice, classification:Bivalve Pokémon, height_m:1.5, weight_kg:132.5, abilities:Shell Armor, description:Its shell is extremely hard. It cannot be shattered, even with a bomb. The shell opens only when it is attacking.

national_number:92, gen:I, name:Gastly, primary_type:ghost, secondary_type:poison, classification:Gas Pokémon, height_m:1.3, weight_kg:0.1, abilities:Levitate, description:Born from gases, anyone would faint if engulfed by its gaseous body, which contains poison.

national_number:93, gen:I, name:Haunter, primary_type:ghost, secondary_type:poison, classification:Gas Pokémon, height_m:1.6, weight_kg:0.1, abilities:Levitate, description:Its tongue is made of gas. If licked, its victim starts shaking constantly until death eventually comes.

national_number:94, gen:I, name:Gengar, primary_type:ghost, secondary_type:poison, classification:Shadow Pokémon, height_m:1.5, weight_kg:40.5, abilities:Cursed Body, description:On the night of a full moon, if shadows move on their own and laugh, it must be Gengar's doing.

national_number:95, gen:I, name:Onix, primary_type:rock, secondary_type:ground, classification:Rock Snake Pokémon, height_m:8.8, weight_kg:210, abilities:Rock Head, description:As it digs through the ground, it absorbs many hard objects. This is what makes its body so solid.

national_number:96, gen:I, name:Drowzee, primary_type:psychic, classification:Hypnosis Pokémon, height_m:1, weight_kg:32.4, abilities:Insomnia, description:If you sleep by it all the time, it will sometimes show you dreams it had eaten in the past.

national_number:97, gen:I, name:Hypno, primary_type:psychic, classification:Hypnosis Pokémon, height_m:1.6, weight_kg:75.6, abilities:Insomnia, description:Avoid eye contact if you come across one. It will try to put you to sleep by using its pendulum.

national_number:98, gen:I, name:Krabby, primary_type:water, classification:River Crab Pokémon, height_m:0.4, weight_kg:6.5, abilities:Hyper Cutter, description:It can be found near the sea. The large pincers grow back if they are torn out of their sockets.

national_number:99, gen:I, name:Kingler, primary_type:water, classification:Pincer Pokémon, height_m:1.3, weight_kg:60, abilities:Hyper Cutter, description:Its large and hard pincer has 10,000-horsepower strength. However, being so big, it is unwieldy to move.
100,I,Voltorb,electric,Ball Pokémon,0.5,10.4,Soundproof,It is said to camouflage itself as a Poké Ball. It will self-destruct with very little stimulus.
101,I,Electrode,electric,Ball Pokémon,1.2,66.6,Soundproof,Stores electrical energy inside its body. Even the slightest shock could trigger a huge explosion.
